    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Alright, so indeed it's a mix of fetching not being triggered + we delete the chat and messages from the DB when we leave.\n\nThe fetch is easy to fix.\n\nHaving the messages still in the DB would help a  lot though, since otherwise we need to rely on the store nodes and they are not super reliable and are way slower. I tested removing the message deletion and it worked.\n\n@cammellos what would you suggest in this case? When a user leaves a community, could we keep the old messages in the DB? Maybe only the last X messages so when we rejoin it doesn't look empty? Or it's better to delete?",
